1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MAKE TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS TO REMOVE REFERENCES TO
3 PRELICENSING EDUCATION, TO PROHIBIT MORTGAGE LICENSEES FROM
4 REQUIRING RECONSTRUCTION COST ESTIMATES AS A CONDITION OF ISSUING
5 A LOAN, TO DELAY THE EFFECTIVE DATE FOR INEXPERIENCED OPERATOR
6 CONTINUOUS COVERAGE REQUIREMENTS, TO AMEND REPORTING
7 REQUIREMENTS FOR INEXPERIENCED DRIVERS, TO REQUIRE ACCEPTANCE OF
8 CERTIFICATES OF INSURANCE AS PROOF OF INSURANCE, TO UPDATE
9 PROVISIONS REGARDING PEER-TO-PEER VEHICLE SHARING, TO UPDATE THE
10 NORTH CAROLINA PROFESSIONAL EMPLOYER ORGANIZATION ACT, TO
11 ALLOW CASH CONVENIENCE FEES UNDER ONE DOLLAR WHEN AN
12 INSURANCE PREMIUM IS BEING PAID IN CASH, TO MAKE VARIOUS CHANGES
13 TO BAIL BONDSMEN REQUIREMENTS, TO REQUIRE BEACH PROPERTY
14 INSURANCE COVERAGE FOR HABITATIONAL PROPERTY CONTENTS TO BE SET
15 IN ACCORDANCE WITH STATE APPROVED RATES, AND TO AUTHORIZE A
16 LANDLORD TO CHARGE A TENANT THE FAIR MARKET VALUE FOR REQUIRED
17 INSURANCE FOR THE LEASED PREMISES IF THE TENANT FAILS TO TIMELY
18 PROVIDE PROOF OF THE REQUIRED INSURANCE.
19 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
20
21 PART I. TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS TO REMOVE REFERENCES TO
22 PRELICENSING EDUCATION
23 SECTION 1. G.S. 58-33-132 reads as rewritten:
24 "§ 58-33-132. Qualifications of instructors.
25 (a) The Commissioner may adopt rules to establish requisite qualifications for and
26 issuance, renewal, summary suspension, and termination of provider, presenter, and instructor
27 authority for prelicensing and continuing insurance education courses. During any suspension,
28 the instructor shall not engage in any instruction of prelicensing or continuing insurance
29 education courses prior to an administrative review. No person shall provide, present, or instruct
30 any continuing education course unless that person has been qualified by and possesses a license
31 from the Commissioner or administrator.
